    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i honestly dont think i can make it to urgent care, it's just so expensive and i'm sure it's fine. it doesn't even hurt that bad, it just looks a bit angry. if i just do the warm soak to draw out the fluid and put on a thick layer of antibiotic ointment, wouldn't that basically be doing the same thing as a doctor would? i just want to manage it myself so i don't have to deal with the hassle of an appointment if it's just a minor thing.",
