      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While home remedies are often used for minor scrapes, the signs you described warrant professional evaluation to rule out infection. Applying thick layers of antibiotic ointment or using warm soaks without knowing the cause can sometimes trap bacteria or worsen certain types of skin issues. Since you are hesitant to seek care, try gently cleaning the area with mild soap and water and keeping it covered with a clean, dry bandage, but please call a telehealth service if you can to get a preliminary assessment.",
      "source": "target",
